        part deliverableTestGateDoDR13 : TestResult { :>> id = "f49fe1e1-4183-4898-95e5-45bb1b992578"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "123b8a0"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-18"; :>> judgedBy = "claudeOpus"; }
        part deliverableTestGateDoDR14 : TestResult { :>> id = "63fec485-9d9e-4065-a299-15ab84caebdb"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "7dbb918"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-18"; :>> judgedBy = "claudeOpus"; }
        verification hfStatusSurfacingAndPreviewDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f15-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f15"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.6.0 status-surfacing + config-preview copy + persistent long-op state (client), real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 335 passed / 2 skipped; tsc --noEmit clean; esbuild build OK). Verified: plugin-wiring statusDisplay case asserts a saved pendingSwitch yields label 'Switching vault…' (persistent switch state, survives suspend since pendingSwitch is persisted). By inspection: main.ts adds the 'Sync status' command (id=status) toasting statusDisplay(engine.phase()) label+detail — the on-demand mobile readout; statusDisplay branches on pendingSwitch before the resuming/idle branches; configdir.ts ConfigDirectionModal intro copy states 'only files that differ change — everything else is left alone, and after this, later edits on either side reconcile normally'. Honest scope: no persistent on-screen TEXT indicator (platform: no mobile status bar, addAction icon-only) and no true diff/count preview (needs a local-vs-server compare) — both recorded as partial mitigations on their Issues. Resolves issueMobileStatusTextless/issueBlindConfigOverwrite/issueLongOpTransientCompletion. Ships 1.6.0."; }
        verification hfConfirmAndSidePickingDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f13-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f13"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.5.2 in-app confirm + side-picking consistency (client), real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 335; tsc + esbuild clean): modals-ui.dom updated to the standardized config labels ('Use this device's' / 'Use the synced version') and still resolves local/remote; settings-ui.dom Sign-out wiring test updated (confirmModal mocked true; awaits the now-async confirm) + still fires signOut. Wiring by inspection: confirm.ts confirmModal() (in-app modal, warn button) replaces window.confirm in vaultswitch (fork/leave/mirror ×3) + settings (sign out); note-conflict + config-conflict 'keep-side' buttons no longer .setCta(); configdir 'Use the synced version' no longer .setCta(). Resolves issueSidePickingInconsistent/issueNativeConfirmMobile. Ships 1.5.2."; }
        verification hfStatusAndWarningsDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f12-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f12"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.5.1 HF status + warning fixes (client), real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 335; tsc + esbuild clean): plugin-wiring 'statusDisplay gives actionable status' extended — read-only idle → {label:'Synced (read-only)', detail:'your edits stay on this device'} (not 'Fully synced'); existing Fully-synced / Synced-(polling) cases still green. Wiring by inspection: renderLight glyph for idle is now the steady check (or 'lock' when vaultReadOnly), never refresh-cw — spinner reserved for connecting/syncing; vaultswitch.applySwitch confirm wording recalibrated (download → 'moved to this device's trash (recoverable there)'; no blanket 'can't be undone'). Resolves issueStatusIndicatorMisleads/issueMiscalibratedSwitchWarning. Ships 1.5.1."; }
        verification deferUxEnhancementsDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f11-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f11"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::confirmation; :>> procedureText = "wweatherholtz reviewed the three UX enhancements flagged as deliberately-not-done at the end of the UI/UX critique pass (obsidian:// protocol handler, setup-wizard state persistence, deeper IA restructures + residual lows) and directed 'record these as declined items' (2026-07-13) — an explicit human disposition to DEFER, not act, for now. No code changes; the deferral is the outcome. Resolves issueNoProtocolHandler / issueWizardStatePersistence / issueDeepIaRestructure as tracked-declined."; }
        verification surfaceSharingAndConflictsDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f10-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f10"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::inspect; :>> procedureText = "1.5.0 surface sharing + conflicts (client). tsc + esbuild clean (no import cycle from main→vaultswitch/accountui — their main import is type-only); full client suite 335 green. Verified by INSPECTION: main.ts registers addCommand 'switch-vault' (SwitchVaultModal), 'redeem' (openRedeem→RedeemShareLinkModal), 'resolve-conflicts' (openConflicts routes note→config→notice), and renames the setup command; settings.ts unconfigured card gains a 'Redeem a share link' button (plugin.openRedeem); startRedeem opens SwitchVaultModal after an already-signed-in redeem. Commands/modals not unit-tested (no command-palette / modal-render seam under the stub; the underlying redeem/switch logic is covered elsewhere). Resolves issueSharingConflictsDiscoverability. Ships 1.5.0."; }
        verification pluginAdoptionRestartHintDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f0f-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f0f"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::inspect; :>> procedureText = "1.4.0 plugin-adoption restart hint + placeholder (client). tsc + esbuild clean; full client suite 335 green. Verified by INSPECTION: settings.renderPluginChecklist computes needsRestart = ids adopted (pluginAllow) AND not in local manifests, and renders a mod-warning banner counting them with mobile-specific 'fully close and reopen Obsidian (swipe the app away)' wording; when ids is empty (server list not yet reported) it renders a 'Checking the server for plugins…' placeholder instead of returning silently. Not unit-tested (the checklist only renders with real Obsidian manifests, absent under the stub). Resolves issuePluginAdoptionSilentRestart. Ships 1.4.0."; }
        verification guardDestructiveActionsDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f0e-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f0e"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::inspect; :>> procedureText = "1.3.2 destructive-action guards (client). tsc + esbuild clean; full client suite 335 green (settings-ui.dom beforeEach stubs confirm()=true so the Sign-out wiring test still fires). Verified by INSPECTION: vaultswitch.applySwitch returns early unless confirm() accepts for mode!=='merge', naming which side's files are deleted; vaultswitch.doFork returns early when this.vaults includes the name and confirm() is declined; settings.ts Sign out returns early unless confirm() accepts. confirm()-gating isn't unit-tested (global confirm has no seam in the modal harness; the underlying switchTo upload/download logic is already reconcile-tested). Resolves issueUnguardedDestructiveActions. Ships 1.3.2."; }
        verification uxPolishBundleDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f0d-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f0d"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::inspect; :>> procedureText = "1.3.1 UX polish bundle (client). tsc + esbuild clean; full client suite 335 green (modals-ui.dom updated to the 'Keep the other device's' label; the removed statusTitle test dropped). Copy/feedback changes verified by INSPECTION against the critique's file:line findings: main.ts recovery messages name Reconfigure/Switch (not the command name); log-viewer toasts prefixed 'SelfSync:'; reload wording → 'fully close and reopen Obsidian'; conflict breadcrumb → 'Settings → Conflicts'. settings.ts max-file-size blur handler (notice + revert on invalid). setupwizard.ts banner <p> gains white-space:pre-wrap. noteconflict.ts button 'Keep the other device's'. accountui.ts change-password warning extended. wizardsteps.ts statusTitle + Phase import removed (dead code). Resolves issueUxQuickWins. Ships 1.3.1."; }
        verification forkVaultDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f0c-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f0c"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::inspect; :>> procedureText = "1.3.0 fork-vault (client, FEATURE). tsc + esbuild clean; full client suite 336 still green (no covered behavior changed). Verified by INSPECTION: main.forkVault(name) = createRemoteVault(name) then switchToVault(name,'upload','',false) — pure composition of already-tested primitives (switchTo 'upload' has reconcile tests; createRemoteVault is a thin transport wrapper), so the fork copies local content into a new OWNED, editable vault and switches this device to it, original untouched. vaultswitch.ts adds a 'Fork this vault' setting (name field sanitized/validated via sanitizeVaultName/isValidVaultName, doFork → forkVault). Not unit-tested directly (forkVault's steps are network-bound; no seam in the wiring harness). Ships 1.3.0."; }
        verification statusDetailAndResumingDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f0b-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f0b"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.2.0 status detail + Resuming state (client, FEATURE), real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 336; tsc + esbuild clean): plugin-wiring 'statusDisplay gives actionable status' — syncing+pending → {Syncing…, N pending}; syncing+0 → {Syncing…, checking for changes} (never bare); resuming flag → label 'Resuming…' for connecting/syncing; idle → 'Fully synced' vs 'Synced (polling)' by realtimeConnected. Wiring by inspection: onResume sets resuming + renderLight; onPhase clears it once phase settles (not connecting/syncing); onProgress clears it when pending>0; renderLight + settings status row both render statusDisplay (label + detail); ui-dom-harness gained statusDisplay/isResuming. Ships 1.2.0."; }
        verification adoptServerPluginsDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f0a-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f0a"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.1.0 adopt-server-plugins (client, FEATURE), real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 335; tsc + esbuild clean): reconcile 'reports the community-plugin ids present on the server (so a fresh vault can adopt them)' — reconcileAll fires onRemotePlugins with the distinct plugin ids from the server manifest (dataview, templater), notes excluded. Wiring by inspection: main.setServerPluginIds stores the set + refreshes settings on change; getServerPluginIds; installAllServerPlugins adopts every server plugin download-only; settings.renderPluginChecklist renders the UNION of installed + server-side ids (server-only labelled 'from the sync — will be installed'; a synced-but-not-installed row shows 'downloads from the sync'), with a contextual 'Install all from the sync' button when there are not-installed server plugins; ui-dom-harness gained getServerPluginIds/installAllServerPlugins. Extends D0025 (accepted by wweatherholtz — 'for a new vault there's nothing to setup the plugins … proceed'). Ships 1.1.0."; }
        verification pendingExcludesDeclinedDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f09-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f09"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.39 pending-excludes-declined (client), real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 334; tsc + esbuild clean): reconcile 'does NOT count a remote file this device DECLINES as pending — reports it as declined instead' — with accepts=notes-only, a server plugin file (.obsidian/plugins/dataview/main.js) is NOT counted in onProgress (max pending 1, the note), IS surfaced via onDeclined, and is not pulled, while the accepted note pulls. Existing pending tests (reports PENDING work / drives to 0) still green (they pass no accepts → unaffected). Wiring by inspection: reconcileDelta applies the same accepts filter + onDeclined; main.noteDeclined logs a coalesced, change-only message. Resolves issuePendingCountsDeclinedFiles. Ships 1.0.39."; }
        verification configSyncPerPluginDirectionDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f08-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f08"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.38 per-plugin config direction + collapsible plugin list (client), extends D0025. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 333; tsc + esbuild clean). Pure/decision coverage carried by configAutoResolveChoice + configSurfaceOf (configgroup tests). Wiring by inspection: configSync.pluginDir (persisted, fresh-loaded); main.ts setPluginSync (adds to allowlist + records direction default = communityConfigDir() else download; read-only→download), setPluginDir (per-plugin override; read-only→download); recordConfigConflict prefers pluginDir[pluginIdOf(path)] over the surface direction for a plugin path; settings.ts renderPluginChecklist renders a COLLAPSIBLE <details> (open when ≤8, pluginsExpanded persists across re-renders) with a per-row membership toggle + an inline download/upload dropdown shown only when synced (read-only shows 'download only'); ui-dom-harness gained setPluginSync/setPluginDir/communityConfigDir. Extends D0025 (accepted by wweatherholtz — 'I like the lighter form … plugins collapsible even if not all one mode'). Ships 1.0.38."; }
        verification configSyncFirstContactDirectionDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f07-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f07"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.37 config-sync first-contact direction (client), implements D0025, real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 333; tsc + esbuild clean): configgroup 'configSurfaceOf' maps each config path to its surface (core/hotkeys/appearance/snippets/community) + null for note/unrecognized; 'configAutoResolveChoice' auto-resolves ONLY a no-base ('conflict-copy') divergence with a pending direction (download→remote, upload→local) and returns null for a later edit (merge/edit-wins), no direction, or no surface; settings-ui.dom category toggle applies via setConfigSurface (harness updated). Wiring by inspection: recordConfigConflict consults configAutoResolveChoice(reason, configSurfaceOf(path), pendingConfigDir) and calls resolveConfigConflict on a hit else prompts; ConfigDirectionModal offers download + (non-read-only) upload; settings master/per-surface toggles set the direction, read-only forces download + starts surfaces off. Implements D0025 (accepted by wweatherholtz). Ships 1.0.37."; }
        verification configSyncEventDrivenDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f06-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f06"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.36 event-driven config detection (client), real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 328; tsc + esbuild clean): plugin-wiring 'a config-related UI event (css-change) triggers a config scan — event-driven, not just polled' (firing css-change increases the reconcile changes() count) + 'a config UI event does NOTHING when config sync is OFF' (gated on configSync.enabled — no needless scan). scheduleConfigScan coalesces (a pending timer swallows a burst), rate-limits (CONFIG_EVENT_MIN_GAP_MS=5s), and guards unloading; wired to workspace css-change + layout-change; the 30s periodic scan remains the backstop. Test harness: obsidian-stub workspace.on now captures handlers so fire() can trigger UI events. Ships 1.0.36."; }
        verification fastCheapConfigScanDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f05-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f05"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.35 fast/cheap config scan (client), real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 326; tsc + esbuild clean): reconcile 'config scan fast-path: an unchanged config file (matching size+mtime) is NOT re-read/hashed' (io.read spy shows 0 reads); 'config scan still DETECTS a new local config file and pushes it' (empty base → pushed, so the fast-path doesn't hide real changes); 'config scan stamps an unchanged-but-unstamped file so the NEXT scan skips it'. CONFIG_SCAN_INTERVAL_MS is 30_000. The app-resume trigger (visibilitychange → onResume → forces a config scan) is wired in onload behind a typeof-document guard (verified by inspection; plugin-wiring tests boot the plugin through this path — registerDomEvent added to the obsidian test stub). Resolves issueConfigSyncMobileLatency. Ships 1.0.35."; }
        verification editorStatusCleanupOnUnloadDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f04-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f04"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::inspect; :>> procedureText = "1.0.34 in-editor-icon cleanup on unload (client). tsc + esbuild clean; full client suite 323 still green (nothing it covers changed). The fix is a 2-line addition to onunload — 'for (const el of this.editorActionEls) el.remove(); this.editorActionEls.clear();' — IDENTICAL to the already-working cleanup in setEditorStatus(false); verified by INSPECTION that view.addAction elements (which Obsidian does NOT auto-clean on unload, unlike ribbon/status-bar items) are now removed, so a reload/update can't orphan them and stack duplicates. Within-run add is already idempotent via the editorViews WeakSet. NOT unit-tested: the obsidian test stub doesn't model view.addAction / plugin-unload DOM lifecycle. Resolves issueEditorStatusIconLeakOnReload. Ships 1.0.34."; }
        verification connErrorAbortsPassDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f03-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f03"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.33 connection-error-aborts-pass (client), real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 323; tsc + esbuild clean): reconcile 'a CONNECTION failure (DNS) ABORTS the pass — one error, not one-per-file' (20 remote files, every pull throws UnknownHostException → reconcileAll rejects, onFileError fired 0 times); 'a single-file error is still ISOLATED' (a 'disk full' on one file → that file in onFileError, the rest sync, no throw); 'isConnectionError classifies host/connection failures but NOT per-file content/read errors' (UnknownHost/getaddrinfo-ENOTFOUND/ECONNREFUSED/ERR_INTERNET_DISCONNECTED true; disk-full/ENOENT/content-verification/unsafe-path false). Applied to reconcileAll + reconcileDelta mapPools (shared connAbort flag) + the config for-loop. Resolves issueConnErrorPerFileFlood. Ships 1.0.33."; }
        verification conflictReadOnlyAndBinaryCorrectnessDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f01-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f01"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.31 conflict/sync correctness (client), real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 320; tsc + esbuild clean): reconcile 'NO-BASE divergence: adopts the owner's version WITHOUT a conflict copy' (read-only field fix — remote adopted byte-for-byte, no copy, onConflict/onReadOnly not fired); 'NO-BASE BINARY divergence (read-write): keeps BOTH — never lossy-collapsed' (F1 — two invalid-UTF-8 blobs that decode to the same U+FFFD string are NOT treated equal; copy preserved); 'an EXISTING conflict copy on a read-only share is NOT reported as won't sync'; existing read-only merge test (base + both changed → copy kept) still green; sharelink 'fails CLOSED — unknown/malformed perm is read-only' (F6). By inspection (DOM/queue-timing not unit-fixtured): resolveNoteConflict re-check before write (F3), startPolling unloading guard (F4), listNoteConflicts original-must-exist filter (F5), modal auto-dismiss gated on isMergeable (F1 second locus). Ships 1.0.31."; }
        verification shareRedeemStoreConsistencyDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5f02-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40f02"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Share-redeem cross-store consistency (server), real-tested. SERVER GREEN (cargo test — lib 93, admin 32, all suites 0 failed; clippy no new warning): shares grant_rolls_back_in_memory_when_save_fails (F2a — a grant whose save() fails leaves owner_grant_count 0 and permission None, so the redeem rollback can't strand a live grant); admin self_redeem_does_not_burn_the_link (F2b — owner self-redeem returns 200 and the intended recipient can STILL redeem and reach the vault); existing share_link_create_redeem_binds_a_grant_and_is_single_use + owner_scoped_and_revoke_blocks_redeem still green. Resolves issueGrantSaveRollback/issueSelfRedeemBurnsLink. Ships in the server image."; }
        verification shareLinkRedeemConsumeLastDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50ff-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400ff"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.30 server share-link redeem consume-last, real-tested (server). SERVER GREEN (cargo test — lib 92, admin integration 31, all suites 0 failed; cargo clippy adds no new warning): sharelinks::tests::unredeem_rolls_back_a_claim_so_a_failed_grant_does_not_burn_the_link — a claimed link isn't redeemable until unredeem() restores it, then it's re-redeemable (invite not burned), single-use still holds for a genuine consume, and unredeem of an unknown token is a no-op; existing create_then_redeem_once_binds_and_consumes + share_link_create_redeem_binds_a_grant_and_is_single_use + owner_scoped_and_revoke_blocks_redeem stay green. Handler wiring verified by inspection (the cap path needs 1000 grants to fixture, impractical): admin::share_link_redeem drops the shares lock and calls unredeem(&req.token) on BOTH the at-cap and grant-Err branches before returning. Resolves issueShareLinkBurnedOnFailedGrant. Ships in the 1.0.30 server image."; }
        verification shareRefreshedOnConnectDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50ee-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400ee"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.30 share-permission-refresh-on-connect, real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest full suite 316; tsc + esbuild clean): sharelink.test 'resolveShareGrant — cached permission is a projection of the server grant' — an owned vault (empty owner) is notShared (no extra call); read→read-only; readWrite-upgrade reflected even when the client cached read-only; a grant absent from the list is revoked (owner removed access). Wiring: connect() calls refreshShareGrant(token) after the health check and before the first reconcile, updating settings.vaultReadOnly and throwing on revocation with a clear card message (files untouched, one-shot toast, auto-recovers on re-grant). Kills the vaultOwner/vaultReadOnly dual-source found in the client audit. Ships 1.0.30."; }
        verification conflictModelDerivedFromVaultDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50dd-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400dd"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.29 conflict-model re-architecture (D0024), real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest; tsc + esbuild clean): base/reconcile 'deriveNoteConflicts — the SINGLE source of truth': derives conflicts from the vault file list, ignores ordinary AND look-alike user files (no 14-digit ts), and a removed copy simply drops out (no stale entry); existing originalOfConflictCopy safety cases still green; modals-ui.dom conflict + settings-ui.dom still green. Changes: settings.noteConflicts array + recordNoteConflict/clearNoteConflict removed; listNoteConflicts = deriveNoteConflicts(vault paths); resolveNoteConflict idempotent (guards a missing copy); onConflict just logs + refreshes the projected count. Implements D0024 (accepted by wweatherholtz). Ships 1.0.29."; }
        verification pendingProgressAndConflictResilienceDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50dc-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400dc"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.28 pending-progress + conflict-modal resilience, real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest 310 passed; tsc + esbuild clean): reconcile.test 'reports PENDING work (not files examined) and drives to 0' (3 real transfers → 3 pending → 0) + 'an already-in-sync vault reports 0 pending' (total files irrelevant); syncstate 'Syncing… <detail>' still green. Changes: onProgress single-arg (pending); reconcileAll pre-classifies pending from remote-hash≠base / real tombstones / new-local; reconcileDelta counts the changed set; main.ts shows 'N pending'. NoteConflictModal auto-dismiss wraps EACH entry in try/catch so a stale 'File does not exist' entry is skipped, not fatal (fixes 'Couldn't load conflicts'). Ships 1.0.28."; }
        verification conflictModalFixAndSyncProgressDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50db-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400db"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.27 conflict-modal display fix + sync progress, real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest 309 passed; tsc + esbuild clean): reconcile.test 'reconcileAll reports onProgress and finishes at done===total'; syncstate.test 'syncing tip includes the progress detail (Syncing… 12/174)'; existing modals-ui.dom conflict + settings-ui.dom still green. Changes: NoteConflictModal.run() shows an immediate placeholder + progress-counted cosmetic auto-dismiss + try/catch (no more blank body); reconcileAll fires onProgress(done,total); main.ts throttles to integer-% and exposes syncProgressText(); syncstate light('syncing', detail) + settings status row + tooltip render 'Syncing… N/M'. Ships 1.0.27."; }
        verification falseEolConflictFixAndDiffDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50da-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400da"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.26 false-EOL-conflict fix + diff view, real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest 307 passed; tsc + esbuild clean): reconcile.test 'sameIgnoringEol' (CRLF/LF + trailing-newline cosmetic; real edits/added lines not) + 'no-base divergence that is ONLY line endings -> converge on remote, NO conflict copy' (asserts zero (conflict… copies + local converges to the remote bytes); merge.test 'unifiedLineDiff' (context/−other/+this-device; EOL-only = zero changed lines). Fix: sameIgnoringEol guard in reconcileOne merge/conflict-copy branch. UX: NoteConflictModal auto-dismisses cosmetic copies + renders a real line diff (unifiedLineDiff via exported merge.lcsPairs). Root cause: independent identical copies (Windows CRLF vs mobile LF) + no common base on first sync/adopt. Ships 1.0.26."; }
        verification granteeLeaveShareDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50d9-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400d9"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.25 grantee leave/decline a share, real-tested (server+client). SERVER GREEN (cargo test 149: 91 lib + 31 admin + 2 reg + 5 sharing + 21 sync) with the new DELETE /api/shared (api::leave_share, grantee forced to caller, audited). E2E GREEN against the real server (sharing-e2e, 2 tests, ~17s): the extended must-change→redeem-link→sync test now also asserts the grantee's owner-qualified route is 200 before leaving, LEAVE succeeds, then 403 after, and the vault is gone from listShared. CLIENT: transport.leaveShare + plugin.leaveSharedVault (disconnects if it's the current vault; local files kept) + Switch-modal 'Leave' button (confirm). tsc + esbuild clean. Server change rebuilds :latest; plugin ships 1.0.25."; }
        verification settingsPanelTargetedCleanupDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50d8-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400d8"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.24 settings-panel targeted cleanup, real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest settings-ui.dom 9 + modals-ui.dom 14; tsc + esbuild clean): the DOM tests still find Disconnect + Reconfigure (now under Advanced, same container) and drive their plugin actions; RedeemShareLinkModal still routes to startRedeem. Changes: fillStatus drops the Server 'Reconfigure' button + Vault 'Redeem link' + status-row 'Disconnect'; renderAdvanced gains a 'Connection' row with Reconfigure + Disconnect (+ a desc distinguishing them from Sign out); SwitchVaultModal gains 'Redeem a share link' (opens RedeemShareLinkModal → startRedeem). Scope = user-approved 'Targeted fixes'. Ships 1.0.24."; }
        verification redeemE2ECoverageDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50d7-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400d7"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Redeem/share end-to-end coverage, RUN GREEN against the real server binary (cargo debug built; vitest sharing-e2e.spec — 2 tests pass in 18s). New test 'must-change account → change password → redeem a share LINK → sync the shared vault': admin creates a raw (must-change) recipient; loginFull returns mustChange=true and /api/vaults returns 403; changePassword yields a token that gets 200; owner mints a readWrite share LINK; recipient redeems it (grant bound, matchObject owner/vault/perm), appears in listShared, syncs the owner-qualified vault and reads the note; a second redeem of the same link rejects (single-use). NodeTransport extended (loginFull/createUserRaw/changePassword/createShareLink/redeemShareLink/listShared/rawStatus). tsc clean. Test-only — no shipped code change, no release."; }
        verification wizardForcedPasswordChangeDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50d6-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400d6"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.23 wizard forced-password-change, real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest 302 passed; tsc + esbuild clean): modals-ui.dom 'a must-change account is prompted for a new password before any other call' — spies show login returns {mustChange:true}, the wizard shows the New/Confirm password step, listVaults is NOT called until changePassword(server, temp-tok, tempPw, newPw) runs, then listVaults is called with the fresh token. HttpTransport.login returns {token, mustChange} (reads must_change_password); loginRemote unwraps .token. Fixes the 'vaults: HTTP 403' an admin-created account (e.g. wi1y) hit on sign-in. Ships 1.0.23."; }
        verification guidedRedeemViaSetupDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50d5-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400d5"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.22 guided-redeem-via-setup, real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest 301+; tsc + esbuild clean): modals-ui.dom 'Redeem routes to startRedeem' (the modal now delegates to plugin.startRedeem, not redeemShareLink directly) + empty-link guard; sharelink redeemTargetError cases still green (they decide guided-vs-direct). Design: SetupWizardModal gains a redeem mode (opts.shareLink) — server prefilled from the link, no vault-picker, login/register then finishRedeem() persists the session + redeems + adopts the shared vault + reconnects; the wizard paste hand-off prefills in place; plugin.startRedeem routes not-set-up/wrong-server → guided wizard, already-set-up → direct redeem + 'use Switch'. Removes the anti-pattern of needing to be logged in before a share link could prefill/onboard. Ships 1.0.22."; }
        verification redeemNotSetUpGuardAndDirectDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50d4-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400d4"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.21 redeem not-set-up guard + direct-redeem, real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest 301 passed; tsc + esbuild clean): sharelink.test redeemTargetError — empty deviceServer → 'Set up SelfSync and sign in to <server> first' (NOT a new-URL crash), different server → 'This link is for <server>', same server → null. redeemShareLink now delegates to redeemTargetError before touching normalizeServer (which was the surviving new URL('') throw). The setup-link paste hand-off redeems DIRECTLY with a result Notice (RedeemShareLinkModal no longer opened from the wizard; unused imports removed). Ships 1.0.21."; }
        verification shareLinkUrlParseFixDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50d3-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400d3"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.20 share/setup-link parse fix, real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest sharelink + connstr, 16; tsc + esbuild clean): new regression 'parses a real percent-encoded link' redeems selfsync-share://redeem?server=https%3A%2F%2Fnotes2.willweatherholtz.com&token=51f0… → server https://notes2.willweatherholtz.com + the token, where the old new-URL-on-bare-host path threw 'Invalid URL' on the Android WebView; existing encode/parse/normalize/reject cases still pass. Both parseShareLink and parseSetupLink now use URLSearchParams on the query substring (no scheme-swap new URL). Ships 1.0.20."; }
        verification shareCurrentVaultOnlyDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50d2-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400d2"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.19 share-modal simplification, real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest modals-ui.dom 13; tsc + esbuild clean): new 'shares ONLY the current vault, even when the account owns several' — with settings.vaultId='notes' and owned vaults [default, notes, work], the modal renders neither 'work' nor 'default', shows a single Create link, and createShareLink is called with 'notes'; the existing Create-link + Redeem tests still pass. ShareManageModal.render() finds the current vault in myVaultShares and renders one label-free block (title 'Share this vault'); non-owned/not-yet-synced current vault shows a can't-share message; pending links filtered to the current vault."; }
        verification shareUxAndCaseInsensitiveNamesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50d1-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400d1"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.18 sharing/UX + case-insensitive usernames, real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest 26 targeted + full suite; tsc + esbuild clean): transport errText reads r.text so share/redeem errors show the server message not 'invalid JSON'; setupwizard hands a selfsync-share:// link off to RedeemShareLinkModal (prefill) instead of 'Not a SelfSync setup link'. SERVER GREEN (cargo test: 91 lib + 31 admin + 2 reg + 5 sharing + 21 sync): admin.rs usernames_are_case_insensitive — create 'Dana' → stored 'dana', login 'DANA' 200, listed once lowercase, never mixed-case; canonicalization (trim+lowercase) at login/register/users_create/share-grantee, non-breaking (stored keys were always lowercase). Per-vault share sections explained (one per owned vault; 'default' is the bootstrap auto-create — deletable). Server change rebuilds :latest; plugin ships 1.0.18."; }
        verification usernameRuleAndUxDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50d0-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400d0"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Username charset + UX, server-only, real-tested. SERVER GREEN (cargo test 149): sync.rs userstore_register_verify_persist extended — safe_name accepts 'will+tag@example.com' (email + plus-addressing), still rejects uppercase ('Alice'), path separators ('a/b'), spaces, '', '..'. safe_name admits '+' and '@' (both valid URL-path + filesystem chars, no traversal); NAME_RULE constant surfaced in the 'invalid username — <rule>' error at users_create (admin) + register (public). admin_ui.html states the rule under the add-user row so expectations are set before submit. No client/plugin change (admin UI is server-embedded); the :latest server image rebuilds on push."; }
        verification skipOsJunkFilesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50cf-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400cf"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.17 OS-junk skip real-tested (client-only). CLIENT GREEN (vitest configsync.test, 16): isJunkFile + shouldSync skip Thumbs.db/.DS_Store/desktop.ini/.git anywhere in the path (config on OR off) and do NOT skip look-alikes (thumbs.db.md, my.git.notes.md, git/readme.md); the existing .selfsync-part/.selfsync-tmp temp cases still pass under the folded predicate. isJunkFile is an EXACT mirror of the server's vault.rs is_junk. tsc --noEmit + esbuild build clean. Result: the field-reported per-file HTTP 400 log spam on OS junk is gone (junk never attempted, no base recorded → no phantom delete)."; }
        verification vaultNameAndSizeLimitsDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50ce-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400ce"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "1.0.16 UX fixes real-tested. CLIENT GREEN (vitest): wizardsteps.test — isValidVaultName rejects uppercase (matches server safe_name), sanitizeVaultName trims+lowercases so 'Testbrsin'→'testbrsin' passes; settings-ui.dom green with the new 'Max file size to sync (MB)' control; tsc --noEmit + esbuild build clean; full suite green. SERVER GREEN (cargo test 149: 91 lib + 30 admin + 2 reg + 5 sharing + 21 sync): admin.rs commit_over_size_limit_is_rejected (a commit declaring size > Config::max_file_bytes is 400'd at the api layer before reassembly); Config gains max_file_bytes from MAX_FILE_MB (default 512, defensive parse); vault MAX_FILE_BYTES raised to a 4 GiB absolute backstop (the real limit is the configurable api-layer check). doc-sync: README env table gains MAX_FILE_MB + the per-device setting note. Wiring: main.ts maxSyncBytes() reads settings.maxSyncMB (default 200) on BOTH platforms, replacing the hard-coded 50/200 split; over-cap files are skipped (never deleted)."; }
        verification deployComposeHardeningDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50cd-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400cd"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::inspect; :>> procedureText = "Compose + deploy hardening, inspected + config-validated. `build:` removed from deploy/docker-compose.yml → `image: ghcr.io/williamweatherholtz/obsidian-selfsync-server:latest`; .github/workflows/release.yml gains a server-image job (packages:write, buildx, GHCR login, build-push-action pushing :<tag> + :latest, linux/amd64) so the image the compose references is actually published on each version tag. Redundant config removed: DATA_ROOT + BIND_ADDR (image-fixed internal path/address) and the no-op `expose:` gone; only the meaningful knobs remain (SYNC_USER/PASSWORD, ADMIN_BIND_ADDR, REGISTRATION seed, LOG_LEVEL). Healthcheck added (curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:8080/health — /health confirmed in the shared router base, served on public AND admin surfaces, lib.rs) + Caddy depends_on service_healthy. New deploy/docker-compose.noproxy.yml (server-only, sync + admin bound to 127.0.0.1). REGISTRATION semantics verified against state.rs: env seeds .registration.json only when fresh (!reg_path.exists()); the admin toggle persists via set_mode and is authoritative across reboots — documented as such. BOTH stacks pass `docker compose config` (valid). doc-sync applied: docs/deployment.md (stale `expose:` claim, first-run-seed note, noproxy + image guidance) + README env table + quick-start."; }
        verification perfHarnessScaleLatencyDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50cb-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400cb"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "A headless real-world PERFORMANCE harness exists, runs, and produced honest numbers over the real chunk/reconcile engine. client/perf (`npm run test:perf`, separate vitest.perf.config) spawns the real server binary + headless clients: scale.perf.ts measures initial push/pull + no-op rescan by vault size (200/1000/3000 notes); latency.perf.ts measures single-edit A->B propagation as the transfer round-trip via the EVENT path (reconcilePath push + reconcileDelta apply — O(change), corrected from an earlier reconcileAll that inflated large-vault latency). RESULTS (docs/architecture/92-perf-scale-latency.md, loopback + debug build = a pessimistic floor): push 2.74/8.01/27.20 s, pull 0.45/1.36/3.71 s, no-op 41/185/373 ms (scan-skip holds sub-second at 3000 files); propagation flat 20->29 ms p50 from 50->3000 notes (O(change), not O(vault)). Harness GREEN; interpretation + caveats documented."; }
        verification perfDevicePassDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50cc-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400cc"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::demo; :>> procedureText = "The real-device fidelity pass: SelfSync 1.0.15 via BRAT on a real desktop + phone against a real TLS-deployed server, exercising scale (initial sync of a few-thousand-note vault, both devices) and propagation latency (single-edit A<->B round-trip on wifi + cellular, with the WS notify path observed). Protocol + results template in docs/architecture/93-real-device-perf-protocol.md. Done when the operator runs it and the results table is filled; any miss vs the pass criteria files an Issue and routes. NO result until the hardware run is performed (awaits operator)."; }
        verification acceptOpenEnumRiskDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50c9-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400c9"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::confirmation; :>> procedureText = "wweatherholtz accepted (2026-07-11, 'yes do both') the open-registration username-enumeration finding as an inherent tradeoff of open self-registration: de-oracling /api/register (returning a uniform response whether or not a name is taken) breaks the sign-up UX, and open mode lets anyone create accounts regardless. The operative mitigation is guidance — keep registration invite-only/closed (the default), which removes the public register surface. Accepted as a LOW residual with documented operator guidance; the closed-mode register path is already de-oracled."; }
        verification acceptMobileFsyncRiskDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50c8-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400c8"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::confirmation; :>> procedureText = "wweatherholtz accepted the mobile buffered-write fsync durability limitation as a known, intractable issue on 2026-07-11 ('accept mobile-fsync as a known but intractable issue'). Mobile platforms expose no fsync API, so the narrow crash-window (a pulled note lost between io.write and the OS cache flush while data.json persisted, later read as delete-remote) cannot be closed in code without breaking legitimate mobile deletions; desktop fsyncs file+dir before persisting base. Accepted as a documented platform-inherent residual."; }
        verification critResidual2DoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50c7-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400c7"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Two residual fixes real-tested. Client GREEN (vitest): syncstate.test isWsStale (stale only once activity older than the deadline) + plugin-wiring 12 still green with the WS liveness timer wired; tsc + esbuild build clean. Server GREEN (cargo test 27 admin) with require_admin threading the ClientIp — the existing admin tests exercise require_admin on every /api/admin/* route and pass. WS half-open: server heartbeat + client liveness timer re-dials a silent socket. Audit: privileged-denied events carry source-IP."; }
        verification critResidualEasyDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50c6-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400c6"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "The two easy residuals are real-tested. Server GREEN (cargo test): admin.rs totp_code_cannot_be_replayed_within_its_window (a consumed TOTP step is rejected on reuse); mfa_totp_full_lifecycle still green with a next-window disable code. The SC.3.13.13 model wording now describes the real mechanism (per-plugin sync allowlist; execution = Obsidian's enable step). tsc/build unaffected (server-only + doc)."; }
        verification critRoundCmmcDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50c5-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400c5"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "CMMC assessor-round fixes are real-tested. Server GREEN (cargo test 88 lib + 26 admin): admin.rs require_admin_mfa_blocks_admin_until_totp_enrolled (REQUIRE_ADMIN_MFA=1 denies an admin without TOTP, allows after enroll/confirm — IA.3.5.3 now genuinely enforceable); config.rs refuses_known_weak_and_short_bootstrap_passwords (CM.3.4.2 rejects the whole weak/short class); the mfa.rs failed enable/disable now audit FAILURE (AU.3.3.1); ws.rs per-user WS sub-cap + guard release (SC.3.13.1). Client GREEN (vitest): transport.test SC.3.13.8 — token-bearing account calls to an http remote are refused (centralized in httpReq), https not refused. tsc + esbuild build clean. Posture reconciled honestly (3.13.8 met, 3.1.11 partial)."; }
        verification critRoundStdDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50c4-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400c4"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Standard critique round fixes are real-tested. Client GREEN (vitest reconcile.test, 88): a delta tombstone for a present-but-unreadable file does NOT clear base or delete (no resurrection); an R===B delta for an unreadable file does NOT delete server-side; the delete-local restore commits with expectedVersion 0 (CAS); a 'download' switch against a suspiciously-incomplete manifest refuses the mass-delete while a genuine mostly-overlapping target still mirrors its extras. Server GREEN (cargo test 87 lib + 25 admin): existing commit/ws/state suites pass with the commit permit-pool + WS must_change gate added; per-request reassembly bound already covered by commit_rejects_reassembly_exceeding_declared_size. tsc + esbuild build clean."; }
        verification uiFunctionalAuditDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50c3-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400c3"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "UI functional-correctness: every interactive control in both UIs drives real behavior; 9 fixed defects carry regression tests. Server GREEN (cargo test 87 lib + 25 admin): admin.rs must_change_account_is_blocked_until_password_set_then_works (A3), admin_grant_and_revoke_toggles_admin_access, admin_deletes_an_account, admin_reindex_and_prune_history_http_ok, admin_invite_list_and_delete. Client GREEN (vitest): syncstate.test idle-with-realtime-DOWN not green + says polling (P4), wizardsteps.test wizardCredentials does not persist password by default (P1), plugin-wiring.test applyConfigSyncChange kicks an immediate reconcile (P2); e2e-helpers createUser now performs the forced change so the full e2e/sharing/integration-matrix suites stay green. tsc --noEmit + esbuild build clean. Browser-level: a Playwright suite (client/e2e-admin, `npm run test:admin-e2e`) drives the admin page's real click-handlers against a spawned server — 5 GREEN: login+dashboard, A3 forced-change screen end-to-end, A1 sign-out fires POST /api/logout (200), A2 MFA enable reflects ENABLED + shows recovery codes (TOTP computed in-test), registration toggle round-trips + persists. The admin browser suite is COMPREHENSIVE (20 tests, `client/e2e-admin`): every interactive control + indicator. Plugin-side browser coverage: happy-dom DOM tests render the real settings tab + modals through an enriched obsidian stub — settings-ui.dom.test (9: config master/category toggles→applyConfigSyncChange [P2], store-password, editor-status, disconnect/reconnect/sign-out, setup/log) + modals-ui.dom.test (9: ChangePasswordModal, ConfigConflictModal local/remote adjudication, NoteConflictModal mine/theirs/manual, SetupWizardModal render + pre-login guard). Full client suite green (276 passed)."; }
        verification cmmcMfaDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50c2-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400c2"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "IA.3.5.3 multifactor authentication, real-tested. TOTP (RFC 6238, HMAC-SHA1) as a second factor for privileged (server-admin) accounts + single-use recovery codes, self-enrolled via /admin (enroll->confirm) and verified at /api/login; self-contained crypto in totp.rs (no new deps). Crypto correctness pinned to published vectors, not asserted. Tests GREEN: server lib totp.rs totp_rfc6238_vectors + hmac_sha1_rfc4231 + verify_accepts_skew_window_and_rejects_junk; server integration admin.rs mfa_totp_full_lifecycle (enroll -> confirm -> password-alone 401 -> password+TOTP 200 -> recovery code single-use -> disable -> password-alone 200). cargo 85 lib + 20 admin green."; }
        verification cmmcForcedChangeReuseDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-50c1-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d400c1"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "IA.3.5.8 password-reuse history + IA.3.5.9 forced-change-on-reset, real-tested. Reuse: users.rs retains the last 5 argon2 hashes; change_password rejects the current or any recent password. Forced-change: admin create/reset flags must_change; the AuthToken extractor 403s every route but change-password/logout until a new password is set; a successful self-change clears it. Tests GREEN: server lib users.rs reuse_history_rejects_current_and_recent_passwords + must_change_flag_set_clear_and_cleared_on_remove; server integration admin.rs password_change_rejects_reuse_of_a_recent_password + admin_created_account_is_forced_to_change_password_before_use. cargo 81 lib + 19 admin green."; }
        verification critiqueServerHardeningDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5005-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40045"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "server + coordinated fixes land, are tested (cargo), and are redeployed: SEC-2 default-admin-credential refusal (coded + cargo-green, awaiting operator redeploy), SEC-1 WS token out of the URL query string, SEC-MED-1 register-enumeration parity, SEC-MED-2 account-delete data remanence, SEC-MED-3 login rate-limiting, DI-3 commit-before-journal ordering, DI-4 reindex-refuses-incomplete-dir, client SEC-3 no auto-enable of plugin code received over a shared vault. Server cargo tests + the coordinated client release green."; }
        // SEC-MED-3 is realized as an 8-permit argon2 CONCURRENCY cap (bounds the CPU/RAM DoS); per-IP
        // request-rate throttling is a further hardening left to the reverse proxy (documented).
        verification round1CriticFixesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5006-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40046"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Round-1 fresh 3-lens critic findings (18) triaged; 15 fixed + tested + shipped 0.10.17: DI#1 switchTo honors accepts() gate, DI#2 streamed downloads verify per-chunk, DI#3 pull-race conflict-copy, DI#5 event-path bulk-delete ratio guard; CONC#1 single-flight persist, CONC#2 exception-safe applying flag, CONC#3 self-healing WS re-dial, CONC#4 WS MissedTickBehavior::Delay, CONC#6 drain requeue; SEC#1 lowercase-canonical names (case-collision breach), SEC#2 argon2 offload+cap+semaphore, SEC#3 vault cap, SEC#5 512MiB ceiling, SEC#6 generic 5xx, SEC#7 reserved-name reject. 3 dispositioned accept-risk/defer (SEC#4, DI#4, CONC#5). Full client suite 162 green; server cargo 70 green; server needs redeploy."; }
        // OPEN — the 3 deferred Round-1 items (no result yet, so orient shows them outstanding).
        verification round2CriticFixesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5008-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40048"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Round-2 fresh 3-lens critic findings (16) on the 0.10.17 code triaged; 15 fixed + tested + shipped 0.10.18. DI: cached chunks verified before use (closed the DI-2 hole), streamed+racing-create pull guards, pushBytes returns committed bytes for merge base, conflict copies preserve current disk bytes, accepted-only bulk-delete denominator. CONC: drainPending runs on every path (no stranded edit under a green light), direct-op failure re-queues, version cursor ASSIGN not max (rewind converges), WS-redial races (stale-timer cancel, no-backoff-inflate on lock-defer, escalate never-opened socket). SEC: case-insensitive self-folder exclusion (cred-hijack), junk-name reject (reindex-brick), WS ACL re-check on revoke, admin users_create argon2 cap. 1 accepted (residual large-file pull TOCTOU, inherent). Full client suite 163 green; server cargo 71 green; server needs redeploy."; }
        verification fsmRefactorDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-500e-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4004e"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "A timing/event-driven architecture critique found the client's REAL control state lived in scattered imperative booleans (applying/connecting/remoteDirty/pendingLocal) with the queue-drain dance re-implemented at six async entry points — the source of the whole CONC-R* race family — while syncstate.ts's FSM only drove the light. Extracted SyncEngine (syncengine.ts): the ONE authoritative operational machine — a single serial event queue with run-to-completion semantics, effects injected (fully unit-testable, 11 tests). Rewired main.ts to it: vault/WS/poll events are PRODUCERS that enqueue; connect/reconcile/reconcilePath/rews/teardown are EFFECTS; the light is a pure PROJECTION of the engine phase. Removed applying/connecting/remoteDirty/pendingLocal/wsRedialTimer/drainPending/onRemoteChanged/poll + all six try/finally blocks. Result: the redial-vs-reconnect race, mid-reconcile-poke drop, drain-stranding, and leaked-guard wedge are impossible by construction. Behavior-equivalent to 0.10.23 (same connect/reconcile/backoff/config-scan logic). tsc clean; full client suite 174 green (163 + 11 engine); shipped 0.10.24. The main.ts WIRING itself remains un-unit-tested (issueOrchestrationUntested, materially reduced — the engine core is now the testable unit)."; }
        verification pluginShareOptInDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-500d-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4004d"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Community-plugin sync flipped from a denylist (default-share; a new install auto-pushed + could overwrite peers) to an ALLOWLIST (ConfigSyncSelection.pluginAllow): shouldSync gates a plugin folder on explicit opt-in, the self-folder exclusion still overrides the allowlist, DEFAULT is empty (nothing shared until opted in). Settings shows a per-plugin checklist (check=share) + bulk Share-all/Share-none + an N/M count; loadSettings backfills pluginAllow:[] for upgraded installs. configsync unit tests updated (self-exclusion strengthened to prove it beats the allowlist; a new/non-allowlisted plugin does NOT sync) + e2e opt dataview in; full client suite 163 green; shipped 0.10.23."; }
        verification round5CriticFixesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-500b-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4004b"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Round-5 (holistic + final-adversary) on 0.10.20: the final cross-boundary adversary found 5 LOW/LOW-MED (none above MED on Linux) and VERIFIED the cross-cutting invariants sound (reconstruction parity, cursor-ASSIGN, WS ACL, drain/remoteDirty, persist, argon2, canonical-path no-false-reject). 3 correctness fixes shipped 0.10.21: DI-R5#1 Unicode case-collision fold (+test), DI-R5#4 legacy invalid-name key still deletable (+test), SEC-R5#2 revoke-tokens-before-purge. The holistic completeness reviewer's verdict: the data-safety core ('a note is never silently lost') holds across all traced permutations and is well-tested; the system is production-ready for a careful self-hoster who upgrades client+server in lockstep. cargo 74 green; client 163 green."; }
        // OPEN — the completeness/robustness enhancements from the holistic round (no result yet).
        verification round5CompletenessFollowupsDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-500c-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4004c"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "NOTE (0.10.26): items (1) version handshake, (3) admin reindex, and (4) commit CAS SHIPPED under preReleaseHardening and are re-pointed there; this action now tracks only the REMAINDER — (2) test-harness the imperative orchestration layer (materially reduced by the FSM refactor + the new version/auth wiring tests, but the raw-event config pipeline + SEC-3 gate + WS revocation eviction still lack direct tests), (5) persisted-data forward-migration + (6) lazy-GC wording, and (7) the cosmetic conflict-copy edges. Original scope: (1) client<->server protocol/schema VERSION negotiation (server advertises an apiVersion + index schema tag; client checks on connect and surfaces a clear 'incompatible — upgrade' message instead of an undiagnosable retry loop) — the most likely real-world breakage for a self-hoster who auto-updates the plugin independently of the server. (2) test-harness the imperative main.ts orchestration layer (reconnect FSM, raw-event live-config pipeline, drain/remoteDirty, the SEC-3 shared-vault plugin-code gate, WS instant-push + revocation eviction) — extract into injectable units like the pure modules; this is the 0.10.4-escape code family and is currently inspect+attestation only. (3) admin-surface reindex for a shared/non-owned corrupt vault (today owner-only via curl). (4) optimistic-concurrency (expected_version/if-match) on commit to close the exact-simultaneous double-first-commit lost-update on a shared RW vault. (5) explicit persisted-data forward-migration for client base/settings + a server index schema version. (6) tighten the 'startup orphan GC' requirement wording to 'lazy first-access GC' (idle vaults GC on first open, not at boot). (7) cosmetic: streamed conflictCopyIfRaced can leave an orphan copy if the stream then throws; merge-fallback conflict tag can mismatch content on a racing save. Each lands with tests. SHIPPED 0.10.33 (10a7154): item 7 fixed (conflictCopyIfRaced returns the copy path → applyPull removes the orphan on stream-fail + skips the fallthrough double-copy; conflict copies tagged with the live-local hash), items 5/6 fixed (client data.json schemaVersion + migratePersisted seam; server SQLite schema_version meta; durable-index requirement re-worded to lazy first-access + runtime GC), item 2 fixed (a plugin-wiring test drives the raw-event config pipeline incl. the self-folder security filter). Items 1/3/4 shipped earlier under preReleaseHardening. Server 58 lib + 18 integration + 22 e2e green + clippy clean; client reconcile + plugin-wiring specs green (raw-event pipeline included); tsc + build clean."; }
        verification round4CriticFixesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-500a-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4004a"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Round-4 fresh 3-lens critics on the 0.10.19 code: SECURITY lens CONVERGED (0 findings — critic traced every attack surface and confirmed all prior fixes present+correct); DI 1 MEDIUM + CONC 1 LOW, both fixed + shipped 0.10.20. DI-R4#1: safe_rel_path rejects non-canonical paths (notes//a.md, trailing slash) so the raw index key can't alias/desync from the Path-normalized on-disk name (+test). CONC-R4#1: remoteDirty instant re-run centralized into drainPending's exit so every applying-releasing path gets the WS instant property. 1 sub-LOW cosmetic accepted (transient green light while polling briefly stopped, self-correcting). Convergence: 18→16→8→2 findings. Full client suite 163 green; server cargo 73 green; server needs redeploy."; }
        verification round3CriticFixesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5009-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40049"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Round-3 fresh 3-lens critic findings (8) on the 0.10.18 code triaged; 6 fixed + tested + shipped 0.10.19. DI-R3#1 (MED-HIGH): clean auto-merge re-reads current disk (liveLocal) so a racing local save isn't dropped (closed the DI-R2#5 gap in the merge branch). CONC: scheduleReconnect cancels a pending WS redial (R3#1); a remote poke mid-reconcile is noted+re-run via remoteDirty (R3#3); the WS Lagged arm re-checks the ACL (R3#2). SEC: safe_rel_path rejects trailing-dot/space+all-dot names — Windows-strip index/disk desync (R3#1, +test); users_delete purges data before removing the account row + hard-errors on failure (R3#2). 2 deferred (DI streamed whole-file hash needs a streaming digest unavailable in the client runtime; reindex single-chunk needs a Rust CDC chunker). Full client suite 163 green; server cargo 72 green; server needs redeploy."; }
        verification round7RecoveryFixesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5014-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40054"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Round-7 recovery/operability critique fixes, shipped 0.10.28. RC-2 (High): reindex re-materializes a file missing from disk but present in the AUTHORITATIVE chunk store (the common failed-mirror-write case — no data loss) instead of bricking the whole-vault repair; only files whose chunks are ALSO gone are truly lost and abort the reindex (DI-4 safety) unless an admin passes force (drops the provably-lost so the rest is repaired). admin reindex gains a force flag + the admin UI a force checkbox. RC-3 (Med): a 404 on connect (vault deleted/renamed server-side) surfaces an actionable 'this vault no longer exists — re-create or switch' instead of an endless retry. RC-4 (Med): per-vault admin delete (DELETE /api/admin/vault + admin-UI button). RC-1 (corrupt-reindex tombstone loss) folds into historyRebase; RC-5 (base-persist-failure conflict proliferation) tracked. Server 47 lib + integration green (new reindex_recovers_from_store_and_force_drops_truly_lost) + clippy clean; client 168 unit + 21 e2e green; tsc + build clean."; }
        verification resourceScaleFixesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5018-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40058"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "RS-1 + RS-4, shipped 0.10.30, storage-independent. RS-1: the per-(user,vault) handle map now evicts IDLE handles (not accessed within 10 min) that have NO live WS subscribers when it reaches MAX_CACHED_VAULTS (256) — bounding server RAM (was insert-only). Safe (active/subscribed vaults kept via handle_in_use; an evicted vault re-opens from disk; an in-flight op holds its own Arc) + non-thrashing (idle window >> the 4s poll). RS-4: setBase keeps merge-ancestor TEXT only for mergeable files <= MAX_BASE_TEXT_BYTES (1 MiB); larger text files fall back to hash-only base (still sync; conflict-copy instead of 3-way-merge on divergence) — bounding client RAM + data.json size. Server 48 lib (new idle_handle_evictable_unless_subscribed_or_recent) + integration + 21 e2e green, clippy clean; client 172 unit (new RS-4 base-cap) green; tsc + build clean."; }
        verification incrementalReconcileDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5017-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40057"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "RS-3, shipped 0.10.29. On a remote poke, doReconcileAll reconciles ONLY the delta's changed paths via reconcileDelta (delta.upserts + delta.deletes) instead of the full reconcileAll (changes(0) + a re-hash of every local file). Deletes arrive as explicit tombstones (positive evidence); a suspicious fraction of accepted base tombstoned at once is still bulk-delete-guarded; per-file errors isolated; cursor assigned (rewind-safe). The full reconcileAll is reserved for the periodic config scan + a version rewind (mass-loss signature). Client-only + storage-independent. Client 171 unit tests (new: reconcileDelta reconciles only the delta's paths / applies a tombstone / guards a mass-tombstone) + 21 e2e green; tsc + build clean."; }
        verification sqliteMigrationDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5016-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40056"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Per D0018: the server index is per-vault SQLite (WAL) behind a narrow IndexStore seam, replacing .sync-index.json + .sync-index.log. Done when: an embedded SQLite dep + the IndexStore module exist; the schema (files/deletions/chunk_refs/version + a history-horizon table) is version-indexed with WAL; Vault persistence is ported (commit/delete = row writes with no whole-index clone [RS-2], changes(since) = an indexed query [RS-5], no full snapshot [RS-6], bounded cold-open [RS-7]); the JSON->SQLite forward migration was WAIVED by owner attestation (2026-07-07, 'no real data lives on the server — nuke away'): a fresh SQLite index starts empty and reindex rebuilds it from the authoritative chunk store + bind-mount mirror, so a corrupt/absent DB is quarantined (.corrupt) + opened in ERROR, then reindex repairs; and the server unit + sync suites are green on the new store. Corruption blast radius materially reduced (WAL + page checksums). SHIPPED (steps 8d96882 store / 15b2795 store-ext / 91f2397 Vault port / 05e655b e2e-teardown fix): Vault ported onto SqliteIndex behind the seam (D0018) — the whole JSON snapshot + append-only journal machinery (Index/JournalRecord/replay_journal/persist/snapshot/decref_collect) deleted; commit/delete = atomic row-level SQLite transactions (no whole-index clone [RS-2]; the transaction IS the durability + all-or-nothing the journal+manual-rollback gave), changes(since) = a version-indexed query [RS-5], no full snapshot [RS-6], bounded cold-open [RS-7]; reindex rebuilds via replace_files keeping every Round-6/7 behavior (prefer authoritative store over stale mirror, RC-2 recover-from-store, force-drop truly-lost, version-preserving, path-collision guard); the protocol/api.rs/admin.rs/client are untouched (format swap behind the Vault seam). Server 53 lib + 18 integration tests green + clippy clean; client 193 unit + real-server e2e green (E2E teardown now awaits server exit before rm — SQLite holds the DB open past kill on Windows); tsc + build clean. Postgres stays deferred behind the seam."; }
        verification serverConcurrencyResidualDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5021-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40061"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "The two MED concurrency findings deferred from critique-R8. issueDoubleOpenRace: two concurrent first-accesses to a cold, corrupt vault both run reindex on separate SQLite connections → one hits SQLITE_BUSY and its Vault stays corrupt; if that handle wins the ns-map or_insert race, sync 503s until a manual reindex. Fix = a per-(user,vault) open lock so only one thread opens/reindexes. issueChangesOnAsyncWorker: a full-manifest changes(since=0) whole-table scan runs under the RwLock read guard on the async worker (unlike the write ops, which use spawn_blocking) → a large-vault first sync blocks a runtime worker. Fix = offload the full-manifest read to the blocking pool. DONE: issueDoubleOpenRace fixed via the per-(user,vault) open lock + double-checked cache in state.rs::vault() (test: state::concurrent_cold_open_of_one_vault_opens_once_and_shares_a_single_handle — 16 threads pounce on one cold vault, all succeed, all share one handle); issueChangesOnAsyncWorker verified ALREADY offloaded (api.rs changes() wraps rlock+scan in blocking()/spawn_blocking, the R10-D3 fix). Full server suite 172 passed (cargo test); the double-open corrupt-BUSY race is timing-dependent + LOW likelihood, so the fix is structural (correct-by-construction) with the concurrent-open path guarded by the test."; }
        part serverConcurrencyResidualDoDR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "395f8c76-2d46-424a-97b7-1f833e39b2c6"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "a0dfd0a"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-15"; :>> judgedBy = "ai"; }
        verification critiqueR8FixesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5020-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40060"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::critique; :>> procedureText = "Fresh independent 4-lens critique (data-integrity, security, concurrency, correctness) vs the D0018/D0019/D0021/D0022 code, findings adversarially verified against the source before fixing. CONFIRMED + FIXED (shipped 0.10.35, 6f19f71): DI-H1 HIGH (history-reset detection + notice bypassed on the connect path → silent resurrection of deleted files after a server floor-advance; unified detection across connect+poll — reconcileAll returns its ChangesResponse, reconcileFull wires onKeptAbsent on connect, noteHistory detects/notifies/records on both paths). Conc-H1 HIGH (cold-open auto-reindex, a whole-vault rehash, ran inline on the async worker via scoped() → scoped() made async + open offloaded to spawn_blocking). Correctness HIGH (owner Delete-vault 404 in split — /api/vault was public-only but its button is on the private admin page → moved to shared routes). DI-M1/M2/M3 MED (floor recorded before the poll short-circuit; persisted per-vault lastVersions so a rewind survives a restart; floor bumps only when tombstones were genuinely lost, not on a dangling-ref repair). Security MED (/api/admin/usernames gated require_admin — full account-table dump in merge mode). Correctness MED (merge detection compares ports; ephemeral :0 → merge). Field bugs: the status indicator held 'Connecting…' through the entire initial sync (markReconciling flips to 'Syncing…' once connected); Docker admin unreachable (deploy compose binds 0.0.0.0:8091 + publishes host-loopback). Critics CONFIRMED sound: public/admin router isolation (registration-enforced), admin authz gating, no privilege escalation, CSRF mitigation, SQLite transaction atomicity, tombstone-authoritative delete, admin lock-ordering (no deadlock), sweep-vs-commit RwLock exclusion. Server 94 tests (62 lib + 6 admin + 2 reg + 5 sharing + 19 sync) + clippy clean; client tsc + 97 unit + 22 e2e green (new markReconciling + DI-M3 + dangling-ref tests). Residual (tracked, not shipped this round): Conc-M1 double-open SQLITE_BUSY race, Conc-M2 full-manifest changes(0) on the async worker, admin-handler cold opens on the worker, orphan-sweep >1h slow-upload (accept), auth_slots shared across ports (accept)."; }
        verification autoReindexDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-501f-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4005f"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Per D0022: Vault::open auto-reindexes where safe. Done when: an empty index + materialized files auto-repairs on open (not ERROR); a quarantined corrupt DB with files auto-repairs from disk; a dangling chunk reference recovers from the bind-mount mirror; a file lost from BOTH disk and the chunk store (or an unsafe/colliding name) STAYS ERROR until a Force reindex; and the admin 'My vaults' panel offers a one-click Reindex per vault. Safe because tombstone-authoritative delete + the D0019 horizon prevent a rebuilt index from causing client deletion. SHIPPED (server, b50012d): open() attempts reindex(false) when corrupt; open-behavior tests rewritten (empty_index_with_data_auto_repairs, corrupt_db_is_quarantined_and_auto_repaired_from_disk, dangling_chunk_ref_auto_recovers_from_mirror, unrecoverable_index_stays_error_until_forced; sync.rs vault_with_orphaned_files_auto_reindexes_on_first_access). Full server suite green (93) + clippy clean. Server-only (redeploy)."; }
        verification adminSplitDeployDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-501c-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4005c"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Per D0021: the admin surface splits onto its own bind address, SAFE BY DEFAULT. Done when: by default (no ADMIN_BIND_ADDR set) /admin + /api/admin/* are served ONLY on a private localhost-only admin address and are NOT reachable on the public BIND_ADDR (which serves sync + /api/login + /api/register + /health); ADMIN_BIND_ADDR overrides the admin address; ADMIN_BIND_ADDR=merge (or =the public addr) serves both on one port (the opt-out); app() splits into a public router + an admin router and main binds the appropriate server(s). Integration tests assert an /api/admin/* request to the PUBLIC router 404s while the admin router serves it, and that merge mode serves both. Deploy docs + an upgrade note (existing single-port deployers set ADMIN_BIND_ADDR=merge). SHIPPED (server, 8951b43): public_app/admin_app split via build(); main runs two servers (split) or one (merge); admin_split_isolates_surfaces asserts the 404-vs-401 isolation both ways; deployment.md admin section rewritten. Server-only (redeploy)."; }
        verification adminPortalEnhancementsDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-501d-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4005d"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Per D0021: (a) a PERSISTED admin set replaces the hardcoded single admin — is_server_admin consults it, the bootstrap SYNC_USER is always admin + cannot be demoted, and POST/DELETE /api/admin/users/:name/admin grant/revoke (server-admin only); (b) the admin page shows registration as a TOGGLE (not a button); (c) grantee sharing does AUTOCOMPLETE + fuzzy match against the real username list (safe on the private surface) with the server exists() check retained; (d) an OWNER can delete their OWN vault from the 'My vaults' panel (owner-scoped endpoint + typed confirmation), alongside the admin any-vault delete. Server unit/integration for the admin set (grant/revoke, bootstrap-undemotable, non-admin forbidden) + owner-delete (owner-of-vault only); admin-UI wired. Re-dispositions issueShareEnumeration. SHIPPED (server, 8951b43): AdminStore (.admins.json) + admin_grant/admin_revoke + is_server_admin via the set (lib test grant_revoke_persists); users_list returns {username,is_admin,is_bootstrap}; registration toggle + grantee datalist/fuzzy + owner delete_own_vault in admin_ui.html. Server-only (redeploy)."; }
        verification deletedVaultRecreatePromptDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-501e-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4005e"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Per D0021: on a 404 (the synced vault was deleted server-side) the plugin surfaces a deliberate 'Re-create this vault from this device' action that calls createVault + reconnects, repopulating the fresh vault from this device's local copy (the existing tombstone-authoritative keep+push) — making today's no-data-loss behavior an explicit user choice instead of implicit. The message still states local files are untouched. A plugin-wiring test covers the 404 → offline + isVaultGone. Ships as a plugin release. SHIPPED 0.10.34 (1881e94): main.ts vaultGone flag + recreateVault() (createVault + reconnect); the settings status card shows a 'Re-create vault from this device' button when offline + vaultGone; the 404 message points to it. tsc + build clean, plugin-wiring test green."; }
        verification residualLowFindingsDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-501b-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4005b"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::analyze; :>> procedureText = "The residual LOW findings re-homed off the round1DeferredHardening catch-all, tracked honestly rather than falsely resolved. TWO are ACCEPTED (won't-fix): issuePullTOCTOUResidual (the pull racing-edit window can't be fully closed without blocking Obsidian's own disk writes; common cases guarded) and issueTransientGreenLight (a sub-second wrong indicator during a poll blip, self-correcting, no data impact). TWO are platform/effort-DEFERRED: issueStreamWholeHash (a streaming whole-file hash needs an incremental SHA-256 the client's one-shot WebCrypto doesn't provide; a non-live path since chunk lists are verified at commit) and issueReindexSingleChunk (server-side re-chunking needs a Rust CDC chunker matching the client gear-hash; operator-only, content stays correct + self-corrects on next client edit). Done when each is either fixed or converted to a formal accept-risk disposition. The two ACCEPTED-inherent/cosmetic siblings were signed off won't-fix by the owner under D0020 (2026-07-08) and are resolved there; this action now holds ONLY the two platform/effort deferrals (issueStreamWholeHash, issueReindexSingleChunk), which stayed open until a client incremental-SHA / server Rust-CDC capability existed. DONE (backlog sprint 2): both capabilities now exist and both findings are FIXED + tested. issueStreamWholeHash — streamFileToDisk verifies the incrementally-computed whole-file hash (streamhash.ts Sha256, R17) before the atomic rename (was already fixed; verified). issueReindexSingleChunk — server/src/chunker.rs is a byte-for-byte port of the client chunker (golden-vector parity: chunker::matches_the_client_chunker_byte_for_byte + client chunker-parity.test pin the SAME vector), and reindex now content-defined-chunks each file (vault::reindex_chunks_a_large_file_into_many_chunks_that_reassemble). Full server suite 176 passed."; }
        part residualLowFindingsDoDR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "65411376-f305-438e-b470-223cd4115a4e"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "a5a766c"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-15"; :>> judgedBy = "ai"; }
        verification historyRebaseDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5019-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40059"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Per D0019, shipped 0.10.31 (8c69b8b). The deletion-history HORIZON fixes the corrupt-reindex resurrection (RC-1) without an arbitrary cap. SERVER: ChangesResponse gains history_floor (serde default → an older server decodes as genesis, never a false reset); SqliteIndex.set_history_floor + reports it in changes; Vault caches it and a rebuild-from-disk (was_corrupt) reindex raises it to the current version (a HEALTHY reindex keeps tombstones + the floor). CLIENT: detects a reset (server history_floor advanced past the per-vault floor this device last synced, persisted in settings.historyFloors keyed owner/vault since state.version is ephemeral; OR a version rewind), routes to the FULL reconcile, and reports every file KEPT because absent-without-tombstone (reconcileOne already keeps+pushes — never deletes without a tombstone) via onKeptAbsent, surfacing ONE batched dismissible notice (full list to the sync log). No data loss ever; resurrection becomes visible + user-correctable. The deliberate operator tombstone-PRUNE is deferred (tombstonePrune). Server 58 lib (new corrupt_reindex_raises_history_floor, healthy_reindex_keeps_history_floor_and_tombstones, history_floor_set_and_reported_in_changes) + 18 integration green + clippy clean; client 195 unit (new reconcile onKeptAbsent + plugin-wiring floor-advance detection) + real-server e2e green; tsc + build clean."; }
        verification tombstonePruneDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-501a-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4005a"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "The deferred OPERATOR tombstone-prune (D0019): a deliberate operation that raises the history_floor AND physically drops tombstones below it to reclaim space, reusing the horizon machinery historyRebase shipped (a below-floor client already reconciles conservatively). Done when an operator can prune (an admin endpoint or a documented threshold), tombstones below the new floor are removed, the floor is raised atomically, and a below-floor client still keeps+notifies rather than resurrecting. SHIPPED (server, 8025fb2): SqliteIndex::prune_tombstones(floor) DELETEs deletions below floor + raises history_floor atomically; Vault::prune_history clamps floor to [current floor, version]; POST /api/admin/prune-history {owner, vault, floor?} (server-admin, floor default = current version = prune all). Server 60 lib (new prune_tombstones + prune_history) + 18 integration green, clippy clean."; }
        verification scaleHardeningDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5015-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40055"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "The resource/scale findings from the Round-7 pass, addressed for scale-agnosticism. RS-1 evict idle VaultHandles; RS-2 avoid the per-write whole-index clone; RS-3 reconcile only the incremental delta on a remote poke (not full manifest + full re-hash); RS-4 cap per-file base text (large text -> hash-only); RS-5 version-indexed changes(since); RS-6 incremental snapshot; RS-7 bounded cold-open. The scale-agnostic resolution for RS-2/5/6/7 is the storage-engine decision (adopt SQLite — indexed queries + row-level writes + WAL/checksums moot them AND harden against index corruption); RS-1/3/4 are storage-independent. DONE: this umbrella is satisfied by the three split delivering actions — resourceScaleFixes (RS-1/4, 0.10.30), incrementalReconcile (RS-3, 0.10.29), sqliteMigration (RS-2/5/6/7, D0018). Every RS-1..7 finding is shipped or mooted; each carries its own green DoD."; }
        verification round6CriticFixesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5013-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40053"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Round-6 fresh 3-lens critique (independent data-integrity/security/concurrency critics) vs 0.10.26; 9 findings fixed + shipped 0.10.27 (1 Low accept-risk). HIGH: (DI) removed the arbitrary MAX_TOMBSTONES cap — under tombstone-authoritative delete it made a long-offline client RESTORE a genuinely-deleted file (resurrection); tombstones now durable (proper bound = historyRebase). (CONC) reconcilePath isolates a CommitConflictError (per-file skip -> merge next pass) like reconcileAll, so a routine concurrent-edit CAS 409 no longer flaps the engine offline (regression from the 0.10.26 CAS work); non-conflict errors still propagate. (SEC) flushConfigReload never auto-enables synced plugin CODE nor auto-applies synced theme/snippet CSS for ANY vault — closes the SEC-3 owner-direction RCE (a readWrite peer's main.js on a vault you own) + the ungated-CSS injection. MED: single-flight freshLogin (no concurrent re-login race / orphan token); failToOffline drops `connected` (a WS redial in the offline window is ignored — one recovery path); reindex applies the safe_rel_path + case/fold collision guard and, when healthy, prefers the authoritative chunk store over a stale mirror (issueReindexBindMount un-deferred). LOW: doConnect clears this.ws before its awaits; path-coalescing keeps the max size. Server 46 lib + 18 integration tests green + clippy clean; client 168 unit + 21 e2e green; tsc + build clean."; }
        verification stpaSuspicionPropagationDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5012-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40052"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Per D0017: keel flags a UCA / LossScenario / SafetyRequirement suspect when a linked architectural element (via #Analyzes / #RealizedBy / #Senses, transitively #Explains / #Mitigates / #Inverts / #Enforces) was modified at a commit later than that artifact's reassessed-at-commit stamp; Hazards + Losses are NOT flagged by an architecture change (only by a Loss/stakeholder/boundary change). Needs: a reassessed-at-commit stamp on the analysis elements (EngineSafety schema addition, human sign-off), the propagation to fixpoint, and surfacing in orient + the safety view + `keel suspect`. Verified by a keel test that edits a controller and asserts its UCAs/requirements go suspect while the hazards do not. NO result until built (deferred keel change)."; }
        verification stpaSafetyAnalysisDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5011-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40051"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::analyze; :>> procedureText = "A full STPA (per D0016, using EngineSafety + the `stpa` skill) is complete when: Losses are enumerated; every Hazard traces to >=1 Loss and has an inverse System Safety Constraint; the control structure is modeled (controllers, controlled processes, control actions, feedback, sensors/actuators, and each controller's ProcessModel beliefs); Unsafe Control Actions are derived across all four UcaType guide words per control action; Loss Scenarios cover BOTH classes (why a UCA occurs; why a correct control action isn't executed / feedback never arrives); and each mitigating Safety Requirement traces UCA->Hazard->Loss and carries a `verify`-linked Test. Rendered via the `safety` viewpoint. Scope = sync data-safety (trusted-server model bounds it). FUTURE SHAPE (owner, 2026-07-06): (a) author the control STRUCTURE as a first-class SysML-v2 model (Controller/ControlledProcess/ControlAction/Feedback/ProcessModel typed refs), not prose, so it renders as a diagram and is itself a tracked artifact; (b) add a REANALYSIS / PARITY mechanism so the STPA can be reassessed against the actual sw & hw it abstracts — list the STPA verification Tests (or the control-structure artifacts) in the deliverable-manifest so keel's suspect/drift machinery (D0050) marks the safety analysis STALE when the mapped source changes at HEAD, forcing a re-analysis rather than letting the control model silently diverge from the code. NO result until performed (deferred end-of-project pass)."; }
        verification preReleaseHardeningDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5010-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40050"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Five pre-broad-release items land + tested + shipped 0.10.26. (c1) VERSION HANDSHAKE: server exposes a protocol/index-schema API_VERSION on /health (now JSON) + the per-vault status; the client (CLIENT_API_VERSION) checks it on connect and refuses to sync on a mismatch with a clear 'update whichever is older' message (backward compatible — an absent apiVersion skips the check). (c2) ADMIN REINDEX: POST /api/admin/reindex (server-admin only, owner+vault) + a 'Vault repair' panel in admin_ui.html repair a corrupt shared/non-owned vault without curl. (c3) COMMIT CAS: CommitRequest.expected_version; the server 409s (ErrorKind::AlreadyExists → Conflict) a commit based on a stale version AFTER the idempotent short-circuit; the client sends its base version on the reconcile-driven push / edit-wins-keep-local / merge-push paths and, on 409 (CommitConflictError), isolates the file via onFileError and converges to a merge next pass — closing the double-first-commit lost-update on a multi-writer vault (authoritative switch/adjudication omit it). (b1) TOKEN-TTL CRUTCH removed: the 30s recently-validated cache + proactive listVaults probe are gone; acquireToken is optimistic and a real 401 drives a single reactive re-login (withAuth + doConnect). (b2) CONFIG-SCAN CRUTCH: the periodic config-aware reconcile fires on a CONFIG_SCAN_INTERVAL_MS wall-clock bound, not an every-Nth-poll count. Server 44 lib + 18 integration tests green (new: commit_cas_rejects_stale_expected_version, JSON /health apiVersion) + clippy clean; client 164 unit + full e2e green (new: 2 reconcile CAS tests, version-mismatch + reactive-401 wiring tests); tsc + release build clean."; }
        verification deleteLocalTombstoneGateDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-500f-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d4004f"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "CRITICAL data-loss escape (0.10.25): pointing a populated vault at a WRONG/FRESH/RESTORED server silently deleted every local file, because delete-local fired on the file's ABSENCE from the remote rather than on a real deletion tombstone, and the one-shot C2 empty-server guard did not survive across reconcile passes (the client's own pushes made the remote non-empty on the second pass, disarming it). FIX: deletion is now TOMBSTONE-AUTHORITATIVE — reconcileOne receives a hasTombstone(path) predicate built from the server's changes().deletes; delete-local RESTORES the file (pushes it back) when no tombstone exists and only removes it when the server genuinely tombstoned it (reconcileAll from resp.deletes, reconcilePath from manifest.deletes). The test harness was made realistic: the fake server now models tombstones (deletions[] with versions) instead of mere absence — the two prior tests that asserted the buggy absence-delete were rewritten, and a DATA-LOSS REGRESSION test reproduces the exact two-pass wrong/empty-server sequence (Welcome.md + 'test file.md' never deleted). main.ts made testable via injection seams (buildIo/buildApi/loginRemote/validateToken) + an obsidian stub + vitest alias; plugin-wiring.test.ts (6 integration tests) covers the orchestration seam; e2e harness repaired (ALLOW_WEAK_ADMIN + createVault for protocol-6). Full client suite 181 green; shipped 0.10.25."; }
        verification round1DeferredHardeningDoD : Test { :>> id = "c0f1a5cc-5007-4a10-9b20-a1b2c3d40047"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "SEC#4: a per-vault stored-bytes quota and/or runtime orphan-chunk GC so a ReadWrite grantee can't fill the owner's disk with uncommitted chunks (today reclaimed only at startup). DI#4: during reindex, when an on-disk file's hash disagrees with a still-healthy index entry, prefer/surface the chunk-store content rather than silently adopting the bind-mount bytes. CONC#5: keep pendingSwitchMode set until switchTo fully succeeds so a mid-switch failure doesn't downgrade an authoritative overwrite to a merge. Each landed with tests."; }

