        action postCritiqueDefectFixes;
        verification postCritiqueDefectFixesDoD : Test { :>> id = "bcf36eeb-f8bc-4ec8-985d-d38a8ea22750"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "The four verified defect fixes from the top-20 functions critique pass (2026-07-17) are implemented and the deliverable suites are green. A1 (client transport.ts): diagnose() reads response bodies via a new tryJson() safe accessor, so a 200 with a non-JSON body (reverse-proxy/captive-portal HTML) no longer throws out of the documented never-throws path; fail-first regression in transport.test ('diagnose never throws even when the body isnt JSON', 2 tests). A2 (server state.rs): the per-key opens lock map is now bounded — release_open_lock drops a key when its last holder finishes (strong_count<=2) and both purge paths clear it, closing the RS-1-class unbounded growth; test state::opens_map_does_not_grow_across_distinct_vault_opens. A3 (server vault.rs): Vault::commit reads file_meta ONCE and reuses it for both the idempotent short-circuit and the CAS check (was two queries; &mut self makes the row stable) — covered by existing commit idempotency/CAS tests. A4 (server api.rs): scoped() maps a genuine vault-open failure AFTER the vault_exists precheck to Internal (500) instead of NotFound (404), so an unexpected IO/DB fault isnt reported as a deleted vault. Server suite 99 lib + integration green (incl. new opens test); client suite 399 green (incl. new diagnose tests). A5 (cumulative delete-guard consistency) handled as a code comment, not a defect. Resolves issueDiagnoseJsonThrows + issueOpensMapUnbounded + issueCommitDoubleMetaQuery + issueScopedOpenError404."; }
        part postCritiqueDefectFixesDoDR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "78bbdffc-ef02-436b-8890-a17c1aacfc69"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "d27a2b9"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-17"; :>> judgedBy = "ai"; }
        action postCritiqueStructuralCleanup;
        verification postCritiqueStructuralCleanupDoD : Test { :>> id = "4a390f19-638a-4c75-a2eb-c1440047c5e3"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "The six behavior-preserving structural refactors from the top-20 functions critique pass (2026-07-17), each committed green: B1 — extracted the copy-pasted reconcile-family primitives (isolatedPass error-isolation loop, runDeleteGuard/isSuspiciousBulkDelete bulk-delete guard, advanceCursor, accepts, baseStatUnchanged) into one home each so the safety-critical contracts can't drift (was duplicated 3-4x across reconcileAll/Delta/Path/switchTo/LocalConfig with subtle divergence). B2 — decomposed reconcileOne (~255 lines, 8 positional args incl. 2 bare booleans) into a dispatcher taking a ReconcileOneOpts object, extracting reconcileEnabledPluginList + reconcileMergeOrConflict. B3 — replaced the switch-arm rmeta! non-null assertions with a checked requireRemote() invariant (kept decide() a pure hash truth table rather than degrading it into a meta-carrying union). B4 — reindex classify_missing() helper carrying (key,meta,verified-body) in one Vec, dropping the parallel recovered Vec + recovered_bodies HashMap and their two invariant .expect()s. B5 — split switchTo into switchDownload/switchUpload (two inlined algorithms with opposite R19/R20 error handling). B6 — collapsed the ~15 copy-pasted transport request methods into apiJson/apiVoid + bearer/normBase helpers, fixing three drifts (inconsistent errText, repeated bearer header, per-endpoint trailing-slash handling). All WHY-comments and documented invariants (R10/R13-R20, C1-C4, DI-*, SEC-DATA, RC-2) preserved. Also documented A5 (cumulative delete-guard deliberately absent on the event/one-shot paths) inline. NO behavior change: green at every commit — server 99 lib + integration; client reconcile.test 109, integration-matrix 17, transport 23, full suite 399 passed / 2 skipped; tsc clean. Coverage floors unaffected (pure refactor)."; }
        part postCritiqueStructuralCleanupDoDR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "605fdb54-e076-45e1-ac17-283ffa956adf"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "4a4609e"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-17"; :>> judgedBy = "ai"; }
        action clippyGateInCi;
        verification clippyGateInCiDoD : Test { :>> id = "3e8acf24-fb6b-4f0b-a3ea-8e4f46cafe8d"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "CI now enforces the SAME clippy gate as the D0101 reverify contract, closing the drift gap found 2026-07-17 (issueClippyNotInCi). A new server-clippy job in .github/workflows/ci.yml runs 'cargo clippy --all-targets --locked -- -D warnings' on every push/PR — the permanent guard (D0047) so lint drift can't accumulate silently again (CI previously ran only llvm-cov + audits, never clippy, so a newer toolchain turned keel reverify red on warnings nobody caught). Fixed the ~7 pre-existing lints in files unrelated to the critique work: audit.rs (redundant i64 cast; items_after_test_module allow for the ClientIp extractor), auth.rs (items_after_test_module allow for the AuthToken extractor), users.rs (map_or→is_some_and), sharelinks.rs (==false→negation), ws.rs (too_many_arguments allow on the internal serve_socket), state.rs (OpenLocks type alias for the opens field), tests/hardening.rs (repeat().take()→vec![;n]). Verified: cargo clippy --all-targets --locked -- -D warnings exits 0; cargo test --locked 99 lib + integration green. Resolves issueClippyNotInCi."; }
        part clippyGateInCiDoDR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "52a322f6-4fdf-4fc3-8898-2a3f09bdc6a9"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "ddb4b78"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-18"; :>> judgedBy = "ai"; }
        action postR2FunctionAudit;
        verification postR2FunctionAuditDoD : Test { :>> id = "c8a7ab9a-2b6c-4153-ba8d-20b5044ac9ad"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Round-2 function audit (D0028 methodology) of the next 20 critical functions — server durability/security core (index_store put/replace_files/delete/changes/colliding_key, chunkstore sweep_orphans/put, shares authorized/permission, tokens resolve, users verify_password/is_password_reused, vault delete + safe_rel_path/conflicting_or_unsafe_rels, api commit/put_chunk/get_chunk) + client drivers (sync.ts pushBytes/fetchFileBytes/getVerifiedChunk/mapPool, main.ts doReconcileAll/scheduleReconnect, syncengine enqueue/handle/markReconciling, base.ts toJSON/conflict-name). Audited line-by-line by 5 independent critics; every audited function carries an // @audit marker and every FIXED function an // @audit-hash stamp (9 total, verified clean by .engine/tools/audit_hash.py verify). VERIFIED REAL FIXES: B-F1 ContentStore::put now fsyncs the shard DIR after the rename (a rename dir-entry could be lost on power loss → an acked commit's chunk unrecoverable; write_mirror already did this + falsely claimed parity) — issueChunkPutNoDirFsync; CB-F1 reconcilePath refreshes the size gate from the live O(1) stat instead of the coalesce-stale queued hint (a grow-then-shrink/delete was skipped until the full scan) — issueReconcilePathStaleSize, fail-first regression added; CB-F2 doReconcileAll stamps the scan windows AFTER the awaited scan, not before (a mid-scan throw left the window marked done) — issueScanStampBeforeWork. IDIOM/CONCISION cleanups (no separate issue): tokens sha256_hex single-alloc, chunkstore sweep_orphans no per-entry String, vault delete remove_file+NotFound (drop exists() TOCTOU), sync mapPool clamps limit>=1 (no sparse-array footgun), syncengine drop redundant connected=false + typed enqueue predicate + collapse markReconciling's two contradictory doc blocks, scheduleReconnect jitter comment relabeled equal-jitter. CORRECTED a critic overreach by verify-before-believing: UserStore::verify is a TEST-only helper (tests/sync.rs, 3 call sites), NOT dead code — kept; finding downgraded. DEFERRED (marked // @audit, no fix): index_store N+1 chunk fan-out + prepare_cached + DRY deref/insert_file, api small-commit RAM permit + put_chunk route body limit, sync.ts SyncCtx dependency bundle. Green: server 99 lib + integration + clippy --all-targets -D warnings exit 0; client 400 passed / 2 skipped; tsc clean; audit_hash.py verify = 9 unchanged, 0 drifted, 0 stale. Resolves issueChunkPutNoDirFsync + issueReconcilePathStaleSize + issueScanStampBeforeWork."; }
        part postR2FunctionAuditDoDR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "017a6351-1ba7-4efb-b185-966391acdfe5"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "ee19ccf"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-18"; :>> judgedBy = "ai"; }
        action postR2DeferredFindings;
        verification postR2DeferredFindingsDoD : Test { :>> id = "4513c924-5ff6-4e3b-8495-ee49da2c8491"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Implemented the deferred (marked // @audit) findings from the round-2 function audit — behavior-preserving, each fixed function's @audit-hash updated (audit_hash.py verify: 10 server unchanged). index_store.rs: killed the N+1 chunk fan-out in changes() (one JOIN query grouping chunks by path instead of a per-row SELECT — a full manifest is now O(1) queries not O(files)); extracted insert_file() (shared by put + replace_files, fold rule single-sourced with colliding_key) and dereferenced_after() (the durability-critical decref-collect shared by put + delete); prepare_cached throughout; dropped delete()'s redundant EXISTS pre-check (DELETE rows-affected is the presence signal). tokens.rs resolve(): log::warn on a swallowed prune/slide save() failure (observability; still fail-closed). api.rs commit() + state.rs: SMALL commits now take a permit from a new generous small_commit_slots pool (32), bounding aggregate small-commit reassembly RAM (~512 MiB) instead of the implicit ~8 GiB the unthrottled path allowed. DEFERRED into the Part-B per-element design-pattern pass (still // @audit-marked, not lost): the sync.ts SyncCtx parameter-object bundle (a design-pattern improvement that IS Part-B step 8) and the put_chunk route-scoped body limit (low; the in-handler 1 MiB check already bounds storage). Green: server 99 lib + integration + clippy --all-targets -D warnings exit 0; behavior identical (all existing durability/GC/reindex/changes tests pass)."; }
