        action pbtPureCoresPass;
        verification pbtPureCoresPassDoD : Test { :>> id = "381d3d84-d7de-4df9-9ed0-4eb42ff35707"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "First property-based-testing pass (D0030, Anthropic Claude-PBT method) over the pure high-criticality cores. client/test/pbt.test.ts (fast-check, 13 properties) asserts curated invariants mined from the code's own contracts: decide (totality; NEVER a destructive delete unless a side is absent; both-present+diverged+no-base => conflict-copy = no silent clobber; one-sided base==local=>pull / base==remote=>push); merge3 (identical-edit + one-sided merges; CRLF-INVARIANCE of verdict + LF-normalized content — the exact class of the CRLF merge bug); chunker (lossless reassembly round-trip concat(chunk(x))==x + determinism + per-chunk hash-correctness, stressed at 40KB x 300 runs); sameIgnoringEol (reflexive + CRLF + trailing-newline invariance); mergeEnabledPluginsJson (GROW-ONLY UNION result ⊇ local ∪ remote — a sync can never drop a locally-enabled id, the config-disable-vanish class — + sorted/unique + idempotent + null on non-string[]). FINDING (the process's record step): 0 counterexamples across all 13 properties — the invariants HOLD; no new bug surfaced (these classes were already closed by prior hardening), so NO Issue is recorded (honest — a clean pass is the computed evidence, not a prose 'looks correct'); the 13 properties are now permanent generative regressions that would catch any reintroduction. Green: full client suite 413 passed / 2 skipped; tsc clean; fast-check devDependency added. Mutation testing (the D0030 sibling) is the follow-on that quantifies residual suite efficacy."; }
