        action mutationTestingSharesPass;
        verification mutationTestingSharesPassDoD : Test { :>> id = "b8e1c2d3-4a5b-4c6d-8e7f-901a2b3c4d5e"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "First mutation-testing pass (D0030 sibling of the PBT pass), cargo-mutants v27.1 on server/src/shares.rs — the authz KEYSTONE (highest-criticality: every access decision). 53 mutants; the honest signal is the SURVIVORS. Run 1 (--timeout 120, ~1.25x the 96s baseline) reported 42 caught / 1 missed / 6 timeout / 4 unviable — the tight timeout under -j2 contention made 6 mutants inconclusive. Re-run at --timeout 300 resolved all timeouts and exposed 4 REAL survivors (a systemic test-gap class, NOT code defects — the code is correct): (1) purge_user:161 `!=`->`==` (skip save()): the retain-then-`if len != before { save() }` deletion methods (revoke/purge_vault/purge_user) were asserted only against the LIVE in-memory store, so a mutant that SKIPS the durable write survived — a dropped grant would reload after a restart (the dangling-grant reactivation hazard purge_vault's own comment warns of); (2+3) revoke:118 `&&`->`||` (x2) and (4) grants_for:136 `&&`->`||`: the exact (owner,vault,grantee) / (owner,vault) MATCH predicates had no selectivity test (every prior test used a single grant or same owner+vault), so broadening a conjunction to a disjunction was invisible. FIX — 7 fail-first killing tests in shares.rs (all RED under the respective mutant, GREEN on correct code): purge_user/purge_vault/revoke_persists_across_reopen (reopen a fresh ShareStore from disk and assert the deletion PERSISTED); open_propagates_non_notfound_read_errors + open_rejects_a_corrupt_shares_file (open() must Err, never silently start empty, on a non-NotFound read error / corrupt json); revoke_is_selective_to_the_exact_triple + grants_for_matches_only_the_exact_owner_and_vault (decoys sharing exactly one field must be untouched). CONFIRMING re-run (--timeout 300, includes the 7 tests): 49 caught / 0 missed / 0 timeout / 4 unviable = 100% mutation score over the 49 viable mutants (4 unviable are `-> Default` return replacements that don't compile, correctly excluded). Score recorded as the serverMutationScore Indicator (M1, method=pulled, D0089). Green: cargo test --lib shares 20 passed (13 prior + 7 new). SCOPE: shares.rs only; index_store/chunkstore/vault (the durability core) mutation testing is the explicit follow-on (NOT covered here — no silent whole-suite claim). Resolves issueSharesPersistNotTested."; }
        part mutationTestingSharesPassDoDR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "b8e1c2d3-4a5b-4c6d-8e7f-901a2b3c4d60"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "49deda0"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-18"; :>> judgedBy = "claudeOpus"; }
        action mutationTestingIndexChunkstore;
        verification mutationTestingIndexChunkstoreDoD : Test { :>> id = "b8e1c2d3-4a5b-4c6d-8e7f-901a2b3c4d61"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Second mutation-testing pass (D0030), cargo-mutants v27.1 on the durability core: server/src/index_store.rs (the SQLite index authority — put/delete/changes/decref/migrate) + src/chunkstore.rs (the content-addressed blob store). --timeout 300, -j3. 89 mutants -> 73 caught / 7 missed / 9 unviable on run 1. index_store was already SOLID (1 survivor of 42 viable = 97.6%); chunkstore's untested error/validation/recovery paths gave 6 (of 38 viable = 84.2%). The 7 survivors + kills: (index_store) migrate:106 `!=`->`==`, the R12-CC1 schema_version stamp — with one live schema version the branch was never exercised; killed by migrate_stamps_a_stale_schema_version_up_to_current (a below-CURRENT DB must be advanced). (chunkstore) sweep_temp:22/24 (crash-leftover .tmp cleanup untested) -> open_sweeps_leftover_temp_files; is_valid_hash:39 `&&`->`||` (malformed-hash rejection untested — a bad-length/non-hex hash must be a FORMAT error before hashing) -> put_rejects_a_malformed_hash_as_a_format_error; get:90 NotFound-guard->true (a non-NotFound read error must PROPAGATE, never be laundered into 'chunk absent' — same class as shares.open) -> get_propagates_non_notfound_read_errors; touch:108 x2 (the R16 orphan-clock reset untested) -> touch_resets_the_orphan_age_so_an_old_chunk_is_spared (proves the contract via effect: a touched old orphan is spared by a TTL that would otherwise reap it). The 9 unviable are `-> Default`/`Ok(Default)` return replacements that don't compile, correctly excluded. CONFIRMING re-run (--timeout 300, includes the 6 new tests): 80 caught / 0 missed / 9 unviable = 100% over 80 viable. Scores recorded as serverMutationScore M2 (index_store 100%) + M3 (chunkstore 100%). Green: cargo test --lib chunkstore:: 5 passed + index_store:: 12 passed. Resolves issueChunkstoreIndexTestGaps. Remaining durability-core module: vault.rs (the follow-on)."; }
