        action mutationTestingVault;
        verification mutationTestingVaultDoD : Test { :>> id = "b8e1c2d3-4a5b-4c6d-8e7f-901a2b3c4d63"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Third mutation-testing pass (D0030), cargo-mutants v27.1 on server/src/vault.rs — the LARGEST + most durability-critical module (commit / reindex / GC / path-safety). --timeout 300, -j3. 138 mutants -> 95 caught / 33 missed / 10 unviable = 74.2% over 128 viable: the LEAST mutation-covered module, exactly where the gaps live. Killed the 8 REQUEST-PATH survivors (the live per-commit/delete surface) with 5 fail-first tests: safe_rel_path:47 empty/absolute path rejection (safe_rel_path_rejects_empty_backslash_and_absolute); commit:524 the strict `> MAX_FILE_BYTES` size gate, both == and >= mutants, via the DISTINCT error, no allocation (commit_size_gate_is_strict_greater_than); commit:541 `||`->`&&` — a right-SIZE/WRONG-HASH body must be rejected, not laundered into a committed file (commit_rejects_correct_size_but_wrong_hash); commit:552 `&&`->`||` — a same-hash but re-CHUNKED commit must not be treated as idempotent (commit_idempotency_requires_both_hash_and_chunks_to_match); commit:576 + delete:615 `+ 1`->`* 1` version bump (commit_and_delete_each_bump_the_version). Confirming re-run: 102 caught / 26 missed = 79.7%. The 26 residual are TRIAGED, not ignored (mutation-testing skill: kill or JUSTIFY, never silent): 21 documented equivalent/impractical accepts + 5 real reindex corrupt-rebuild gaps (issueVaultReindexRebuildTestGaps -> mutationTestingVaultReindex follow-on). ACCEPTS: MAX_FILE_BYTES:13 x5 (the 4 GiB backstop constant — its COMPARISON is now tested by commit:524; the exact value can't be exercised without allocating GBs); verify_and_gc:274/276 x4 (the `reclaimed` counter feeds ONLY a log::info — the reclamation side-effect is separately caught); maybe_sweep_orphans:487/490/494/500 x10 (a 300s-Instant-interval-gated best-effort opportunistic sweep + a log-only n>0 guard; the core reclamation delegates to store.sweep_orphans, already 100% in chunkstore — a clock-injection seam would be test-only complexity on a non-critical path); delete:625 `!=`->`==` (log-only warning on a mirror-removal failure); safe_rel_path:47:47 `||`->`&&` (EQUIVALENT on Windows — the component-split + segs.join()==path backstop already rejects a backslash, so the early guard is redundant there; the new test kills it on a POSIX FS where '\\' is literal). Green: cargo test --lib vault::tests 42 passed (37 prior + 5 new). Resolves issueVaultRequestPathTestGaps."; }
