        action critiqueRPlus1ClientFixes;
        verification critiqueRPlus1ClientFixesDoD : Test { :>> id = "c1a7d0e1-4b5c-4d6e-8f70-1a2b3c4d5e66"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Another adversarial critique pass (4 INDEPENDENT critics: DI/durability, security/authz, concurrency, client-correctness), each finding VERIFIED against the code before acting; the critics also correctly CLEARED the core ACL, path safety, decide()/merge3, chunker, and DoS bounds (no manufactured findings). Two CLIENT data-safety findings fixed + fail-first tested: CLIENT-1 (HIGH, data loss) — reconcileAll's bulk-delete guard counted only delete-LOCAL candidates (wouldDelete = !remote.has && local.has) and gated only that branch, so a mass delete-REMOTE (a vanished local vault: cloud de-hydration / partial backup restore / cleared storage) wiped the whole server vault + tombstoned it fleet-wide; added a symmetric wouldDeleteRemote ratio guard (BULK_DELETE_MIN floor, no empty-local override — a tiny/empty vault isn't second-guessed) gating the delete-remote branch (reconcile.test: a 10-file vanish is guarded, a single delete still propagates). CLIENT-2 (Medium, silent merge loss) — pushBytes wrote merged bytes then pushFile RE-READ from disk, so a local save racing the write->read gap was committed in place of the merge (discarding the remote edit the merge folded in; DI-5 fixed base consistency, not this loss); refactored to a shared commitBytes core that commits the in-hand bytes (sync.test: pushBytes commits the exact bytes given, not the raced re-read). Green: full client suite 416 passed / 2 skipped; tsc clean. Resolves issueMassDeleteRemoteUnguarded + issueMergePushReReadLoss."; }
        part critiqueRPlus1ClientFixesDoDR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "c1a7d0e1-4b5c-4d6e-8f70-1a2b3c4d5e67"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "504238f"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-18"; :>> judgedBy = "claudeOpus"; }
